What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Optical Fiber Components Market?

Market Analysis and Insights

Optical Fiber Components Market

Surge in the evolution of cellular network technology which has offered higher data speeds and lower latency, growing need to manage and analyse organizational data effectively and efficiently and high expenditure for the development of optical fiber component ecosystem especially in the developing economies are the major factors attributable to the growth of the optical fiber components market. Data Bridge Market Research analyses that the optical fiber components market will exhibit a CAGR of 9.95% for the forecast period of 2021-2028.

Optical fibers are commonly made with a glass core and glass cladding and these high quality glass fibers help to save a lot of money. Cost factors, and performance requirements are the major factors that have been considered in the development of optical fiber component ecosystem.

Rising deployment of high speed data transmission solutions around the globe will emerge as the major market growth driving factor. Surge in the commercialization of high speed network, growing number of small and medium scale enterprises especially in the developing economies and surge in the demand for bandwidth and reliability among different industries will further aggravate the growth of the market. Increasing internet penetration and data traffic and growing requirement for internet of things and more connected devices are some other factors bolstering the growth of the market.

However, lack of skilled workforce and technological expertise in underdeveloped and developing economies and lack of standardization will act as a growth restraint for the market. Also, difficulty in managing the failure of passive optical networks (PON) will yet again hamper the market growth rate. Lack of a strong IT infrastructure and less range of network devices connection in the underdeveloped economies will also hamper the market growth rate.

